SLOW MOV CENTRED OVER SEA AREA BAILEY. DURING SUNDAY IT WILL DRIFT SLWY EWARDS
INTO SEA AREA HEBRIDES AND FILL. BY MIDDAY MONDAY IT WILL HAVE CROSSED SCOTLAND
TO BE CENTRED IN SEA AREA CROMARTY 984 AS A TRANSIENT RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE
BUILDS IN THE W. BY MIDDAY TUESDAY THIS LOW WILL BE CENTRED IN SEA AREA VIKING
991 AS THE RIDGE TO THE W DECLINES DUE TO FURTHER N ATLANTIC DEPRESSIONS
BECMG DOMINANT. STRG WINDS WILL AFFECT MUCH OF THE N SEA OVERNIGHT SATURDAY
INTO SUNDAY WITH TEMPO GALES LIKELY AT TIMES IN THAMES AND GERMAN BIGHT.
